From the data info explored, we could see that a good number of columns have missing values in great amount while some have missing values in small amount. For genres column, I would be dropping the rows with missing values. Same with cast,director and overview columns.

Also, colums like hompage, tagline, keywords nd production companies have high number of null values column. While I will be dropping the rest of the columns because of their irrelevance to my questions, I would be keeping the column and fill the missing values with 'Nan' since I would be needing the column for one of my posed questions. This is because, I thought if I drop the rows about '1030', it would affect my analaysis adversely.

In [47]:
import operator
actor_dict = {}
#assign the column of cast to be var actors
actors = df_movies["cast"]
#we use str.split('|'') to split each value and make each rows an array
actors = actors.str.split("|")
#we Create an array.
actors = np.array(actors)
for actorList in actors:
    #print(actorList)
    for actor in actorList:
        #print(actor)
        #clean the white spaces from the left
        actor = actor.lstrip()
        if actor not in actor_dict:
            actor_dict[actor] = 1
        else:
            actor_dict[actor] += 1
In [49]:
sorted_actor_dict = sorted(actor_dict.items(), key = operator.itemgetter(1), reverse = True)
x_axis = list()
y_axis = list()

for item in sorted_actor_dict[0:20]:
    x_axis.append(item[0])
    #print(x_axis)
    y_axis.append(item[1])
    #print(y_axis)

sns.set(rc={'figure.figsize':(12,10)}, font_scale=1.4)
graph = sns.barplot(x_axis, y_axis, palette="Set3")

#rotate x-axis' text
for item in graph.get_xticklabels():
    item.set_rotation(80)
    

graph.set(xlabel='actor names', ylabel='number of appearances', title = 'Top 20 actors based on the number of the appearances in movies')
plt.show()
